<div><h3>Notes from Number Crunching Curtis Stone</h3></div>
<div>Prato Principal 80/20<div>
<div><ul>Have consistant goals
<li>short term</li>
<li>medium</li>
<li>long term</li>
</ul></div>

<div>Why do you want to sell? Why people should buy from you?</div>

<div>Know your market
<ol>Farmers Markets 
<li>What is the market?</li>
<li>How long is the season?</li>
<li>Is there a waiting list or fees?</li>
<li>Shop the market and see what's being sold and demographics</li>
<li>Who shops there?</li>
<li>Who are the regulars of the market?</li>
<li>What are they buying by season and time?</li>
<li>Who are the top vendors?</li>
 </ol>
<ol>Restaurants -- Be dependable
<li>Farm to Table Field to Fork restaurants/local food restaurants</li>
<li>Where do they source local produce from?</li>
<li>Ask about spoilage cost</li>
<li>Niche product for a restaurant</li>
<li>when did they open and how long has the chef been there?</li>
</ol> 
<ol>Restaurants
<li>Matt's Casba</li>
<li>Yellow Dog Cafe</li>
<li>Nomad Cafe</li>
</ol>
<ol>Grocery Stores
<li>Lucky's Market</li>
<li>Downtown Produce</li>
<li>Health Food Stores</li>
</ol>
</div>

